            <abstract>
                <p>The Gadla ʾAbrǝhām is one of the three so-called "Testaments of the three patriarchs". Its Beta ʾƎsrāʾel recensions is based on a 
                    Christian recension. The text seems to be very rare, both available editions, <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/VA7V9TRU"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1922TestAbrBE"/><title level="a">Nuovi appunti sui Giudei d’Abissinia</title><title level="j">Rendiconti della Reale Accademia dei Lincei, Classe di scienze morali, storiche e filologiche</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Carlo</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Conti Rossini</t:surname></author><date>1922</date><biblScope unit="volume">XXXI</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">61–63</biblScope></bibl>and <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/6BANA3I5"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Aescoly1951Recueil"/><title level="m">Recueil de textes falachas. Introduction. Textes éthiopiens. (édition critique et traduction). Index</title><title level="s">Travaux et mémoires de l’Institut d’ethnologie</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Aaron Zeev</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Aešcoly</t:surname></author><pubPlace>Paris</pubPlace><publisher>Institut d’ethnologie</publisher><date>1951</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Travaux et mémoires de l’Institut d’ethnologie</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">55</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">55</biblScope><note type="url">https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k26168q.image</note></bibl> are based on <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFabb107">Paris, Bibliothèque nationale de France, BnF Éthiopien d'Abbadie 107</ref></p>
